On the fourth day of my internship, I focused on identifying and procuring the hardware required
for the development of the virtual piano project. The technical specifications of the components to be 
used in the project were examined, their compatibility with the system was evaluated, and the 
procurement process for the required hardware was planned.

As part of this process, an FTDI USB-to-TTL converter was obtained to enable programming and 
communication with the ESP32-CAM development board. In addition, the other hardware 
components to be used in the project were reviewed and evaluated for their suitability.

By the end of the day, the hardware procurement process had been initiated, and the necessary 
preparations were completed to continue the development of the project.
